"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93434","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-29","<p>The tax changes necessary to deliver the Freedom and Choice in Pensions agenda are contained in the Taxation of Pensions Bill. The provisions in this Bill will apply across the UK as the relevant tax legislation is not, in the main, a matter over which powers have been devolved.<sup>[</sup><sup>1]</sup> The Pension Schemes Bill is being used to introduce further changes relevant to the Freedom and Choice agenda. Where these do relate to devolved matters in Northern Ireland, the Government is in the process of obtaining the necessary legislative consent motion and approval from the Northern Ireland Assembly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] Explanatory notes for the Taxation of Pensions Bill were published on the Parliament Website. Territorial extent is detailed in paragraph 52 http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/bills/cbill/2014-2015/0097/en/15097en.htm</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2014-10-29T15:21:46.8315879Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93434/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93434/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-14","Pensions: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether and how the new Freedom and Choice for Pensioners arrangements will apply to Northern Ireland; and whether they have discussed the matter of a legislative consent motion with the Northern Ireland Executive.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93435","Home Office","false","2014-10-20","<p>The question of whether the new Somali constitution, drafted in 2012, is now in force is subject to ongoing litigation proceedings. A hearing took place recently and a decision is awaited, which we expect will clarify the position.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2014-10-20T14:26:08.3940543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93435/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93435/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-14","Nationality: Somalia","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Taylor of Holbeach on 9 July (HL396), whether the new Somali constitution drafted in 2012 is now in force; and, if so, whether it contains an article prohibiting the withdrawal of citizenship if a Somali becomes a citizen of another country.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99755","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-20","<p>The core armoured vehicle programme budget for the next 10 years is £6.7 billion. This includes the Warrior Upgrade, a new Armoured Utility Vehicle, improvements to the Challenger 2 Tank and the Scout. The latter £3.5 billion order is the biggest Army order in 30 years and will safeguard at least 1,300 jobs across the UK.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-10-20T15:55:37.1622446Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99755/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99755/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what investment his Department has made in armoured vehicle capability for the Army.","false","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","South Derbyshire","Heather Wheeler","905535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99756","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-20","<p>We continue to listen to the accommodation needs and concerns of our Service personnel and their families, and recognise their need for increased personal choice and stability and the opportunity for home ownership.</p><p> </p><p>In April 2014, we launched the £200 million Forces Help to Buy Scheme to encourage and support those Service families that aspire to home ownership. Forces Help to Buy is available nationwide, and has already helped almost 1,500 Service personnel get on, or stay on, the property ladder. <br></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-20T15:58:25.4060529Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99756/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99756/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to increase home ownership among members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Andrew Jones","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","905536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99944","Wales Office","false","2014-10-22","<p>I refer the hon Gentleman to the answer I gave to the hon Members for Ynys Môn and Harrow East earlier today.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb",,"2014-10-22T11:50:27.3520996Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99944/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/99944/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-10-14","Devolution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what discussions he has had with ministerial colleagues on the effects of the Scottish referendum result on government policy on further devolution for Wales.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","905499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92745","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-23","<p>All 128 Access to Work advisers receive training which includes Disability Awareness, Decision Making, Equality &amp; Diversity, Negotiating Skills and Effective Communications. In addition, Access to Work have specialist adviser teams focussing on hearing impaired and visually impaired customers, and also a team to assist customers with mental health conditions. These teams receive additional training, which includes input from suppliers, disability charities and other disability led groups. Also as part of the standard adviser training, staff undertake Influencing Skills and Constructive Conversations training to enable them to work effectively with employers.</p><p> </p><p>Access to Work advisers have standardised work instructions to help ensure consistency during the evaluation and decision making process. However, all Access to Work awards are agreed on an individual basis, taking account of a customer’s disability, job role and the barriers they are facing. Standards are monitored using a Quality Assurance Framework which includes the quality of telephone conversations with customers and employers, and the consistency and accuracy of decisions and financial awards.</p><p> </p><p>Access to Work aims to contact customers within 7 working days and give 80% of all decisions in 15 working days. Time sensitive requests, such as customer support requirements at interview, are prioritised and are supported by a 5 working day service standard. Demand for Access to Work, particularly new applications, grew during 2013/14 and customer volumes continue to grow in 2014/15.</p>",,"Lord Freud","HL1982 ; HL1983 ; HL1986","2014-10-23T15:24:38.7372062Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92745/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92745/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92745/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions"