"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92895","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-16","<p>The latest figures are:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>a) There are 2,856386 Post office card account customers in total.</p><p> </p><p>b) The information is not available in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Information for Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department for Social Development. Northern Ireland statistics can be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm" target="_blank">http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm</a></p><p> </p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-16T14:43:21.8221329Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92895/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92895/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Post Office Card Account","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Post Office card account holders there are in the UK (a) in total and (b) by age profile, broken down by (i) constituent part of the UK and (ii) by parliamentary constituency.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","210281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92896","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-16","<p /> <p>Customers using the Post Office card account as a method of payment to receive their benefit or pensions are not obliged to inform the Department that they hold another bank account. For this reason, the information requested is not available.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-16T15:06:18.3166983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92896/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92896/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Post Office Card Account","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Post Office card account holders there are who also hold another bank account in the UK, broken down by (a) age profile, (b) constituent part of the UK and (c) parliamentary constituency.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","210280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92897","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-16","<p>The sum of withdrawals from Post Office card accounts using either counter services or ATM in each of the last five years is detailed below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><strong>ATM Withdrawals</strong></td><td><strong>Counter Withdrawals</strong></td></tr><tr><td>2009/10</td><td>No ATM service</td><td>84,591,882</td></tr><tr><td>2010/11</td><td>No ATM service</td><td>157,136,419</td></tr><tr><td>2011/12</td><td>4,871,428</td><td>144,266,088</td></tr><tr><td>2012/13</td><td>16,643,172</td><td>133,030,619</td></tr><tr><td>2013/14</td><td>17,654,482</td><td>121,115,527</td></tr><tr><td>2014/15</td><td>932,543</td><td>56,190,911</td></tr></tbody></table>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-16T15:20:25.4023328Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92897/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92897/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Post Office Card Account","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the sum of withdrawals from Post Office card accounts has been in each of the last five years from (a) ATMs and (b) Post Office counters.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","210282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92898","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-16","<p>Balance enquiry figures for Post Office card accounts in the last five years are:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>ATM Balance Enquiry's</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Counter Balance Enquiry's</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>No ATM service</p></td><td><p>1,130,724</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>No ATM service</p></td><td><p>12,721,201</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>4,467,817</p></td><td><p>11,471,310</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>15,427,714</p></td><td><p>11,095,061</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>15,994,130</p></td><td><p>9,897,175</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>8,253,153</p></td><td><p>4,569,642</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-16T14:33:28.9659928Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92898/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92898/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Post Office Card Account","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many balance checks for Post Office card accounts were undertaken in each of the last five years at (a) ATMs and (b) Post Office counters.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","210269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92899","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-16","<p>DWP has not commissioned any research within the last 10 years. However, DWP has worked closely with Post Office Limited implementing service improvements to address changing customer needs. In addition to this, we are currently undertaking small-scale qualitative customer insight sessions to further understand the needs of Universal Credit customers.</p><p> </p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-16T14:55:27.2037865Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92899/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92899/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Post Office Card Account","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what research his Department has undertaken in the last 10 years to examine the needs of Post Office card account holders; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","210286"
