l","210216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92901","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-16","<p>We have followed Gao’s case closely and welcomed his release from prison on 7 August 2014. We are concerned by reports that he has been in ill health since his release, and that his movement is restricted. We urge the Chinese authorities to allow him access to adequate medical care, and to ensure that his rights to freedom of movement and communication are duly protected. <br><br>UK officials have repeatedly raised Gao’s case with the Chinese government, including during the most recent UK-China Human Rights Dialogue in May 2014, and again prior to his release. We highlight our range of human rights concerns in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s Annual Report on Human Rights and Democracy, and the quarterly updates to it.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-10-16T13:33:31.5520565Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92901/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92901/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-10-13","China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the detention of Gao Zhisheng in China; and what representations he has made to his Chinese counterpart on Mr Gao Zhisheng's behalf.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","210079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92902","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-16","<p>My Department has made no estimate of the average time taken to grant access to properties, or of the costs involved, for housing associations to undertake statutory gas safety checks or the costs involved . <br><br>One of the standard conditions of rented tenancy agreements is to allow reasonable access, following advance notice, for gas servicing and safety checks.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","210161","2014-10-16T14:53:24.4822955Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92902/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92902/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-13","Social Rented Housing: Natural Gas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the average time taken to grant access for housing associations to properties to undertake statutory gas safety checks.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","210160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92903","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-16","<p>My Department has made no estimate of the average time taken to grant access to properties, or of the costs involved, for housing associations to undertake statutory gas safety checks or the costs involved . <br><br>One of the standard conditions of rented tenancy agreements is to allow reasonable access, following advance notice, for gas servicing and safety checks.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","210160","2014-10-16T14:53:24.7792273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92903/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92903/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-13","Social Rented Housing: Natural Gas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the costs to housing associations of implementing the legal power to enter a property to undertake a statutory gas safety check.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","210161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92904","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-16","<p>Neither myself nor the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions have held any discussions with the Association of Gas Safety Managers about access to properties to undertake statutory gas safety checks.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Health and Safety Executive provides guidance to landlords on what to do if a tenant prevents access for a gas safety check: <a href="http://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/faqlandlord.htm" target="_blank">http://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/faqlandlord.htm</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-16T15:44:35.6578837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92904/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92904/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Natural Gas: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has held with the Association of Gas Safety Managers about access to properties to undertake statutory gas safety checks.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","210162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92905","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-18","<p>As is the norm for departmental spending under this and previous Administrations, actual outturn estimates will vary from initial allocations, reflecting the activity of the individual programmes within the budget headings and the profile of how money is spent.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Explanatory Memorandum was prepared in February 2013, published in July 2013, and was a snapshot of the notional allocations at that point in time; in turn, it reported on changes from the 2012-13 Supplementary Estimate.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Explanatory Memorandum 2013-14 Main Estimates: Budget Allocations</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><em>£ million</em></p></td><td><p><em>2011-12</em></p></td><td><p><em>2012-13</em></p></td><td><p><em>2013-14</em></p></td><td><p><em>2014-15</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Integration</p></td><td><p>10.7</p></td><td><p>15.0</p></td><td><p>10.8</p></td><td><p>4.1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>I also refer the rt. hon. Member to the Written Ministerial Statement on integration made by my rt. hon. Friend, the Secretary of State (Eric Pickles) today.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams",,"2014-12-18T15:22:43.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92905/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92905/answer","Bristol West","Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92905/answer/previousversion/22311","Biography information for Stephen Williams","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-13","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to Annex B of his Department's Explanatory Memorandum to its main Estimate 2013-14, how the savings in the resource budget for Integration and Tackling Extremism in 2013-14 and 2014-15 were achieved.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","210273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92906","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-16","<p>The requested information is not available centrally.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-10-16T15:13:26.633791Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92906/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92906/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-13","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of new houses completed in the last 12 months in England have been built on sites of (a) less than one ha, (b) one to two ha, (c) two to four ha, (d) four to six ha, (e) six to eight ha, (f) eight to 10 ha and (f) above 10 ha.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","210274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92907","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-18","<p>I refer the rt. hon. Member to the Written Ministerial Statement on integration made by my rt. hon. Friend, the Secretary of State (Eric Pickles) today.</p><p> </p><p>The figure for 2010-11 funding was £30.2 million.</p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams",,"2014-12-18T15:12:24.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92907/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92907/answer","Bristol West","Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92907/answer/previousversion/22308","Biography information for Stephen Williams","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-13","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much DEL Resource from his Department was allocated to integration and tackling extremism in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13 and (d) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","210272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92908","Department of Health","false","2014-10-16","<p>Publication of the Verita reports about the Leeds children’s cardiac surgery unit is a matter for NHS England. A date for publication will be confirmed shortly and interested parties, including Members of Parliament, will be advised. Once published, copies of the reports will be placed on the NHS England website.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-10-16T15:16:07.6240044Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92908/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92908/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-13","Leeds General Infirmary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he expects the third stage review report into the closure of children's heart surgery at the Leeds General Infirmary in 2013 to be published.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","210271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92909","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-16","<p>Departmental statisticians are continuing to develop measures around clearance times and waiting times to ensure they provide a rounded and representative picture of Personal Independence Payment system performance, improvement activity and the claimants’ experience. These statistics will be published when they are ready, with the release pre-announced in line with United Kingdom Statistics Authority release protocols.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-16T15:28:27.1987047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92909/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92909/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the most recent average waiting time is for (a) an assessment and (b) a decision on applications for personal independence payments.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","210270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92910","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>The Department for International Development will be funding the net additional cost of deploying RFA ARGUS.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-16T15:02:47.6195802Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92910/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92910/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-13","RFA Argus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Statement on 13 October 2014 by the Secretary of State for Health, from which departmental budget the costs associated with deploying RFA Argus to West Africa will be recovered.","false","Biography information for Thomas Docherty","Dunfermline and West Fife","Thomas Docherty","210159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92911","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-05","<p>The Department does not have any PFI projects of its own but does provide support to local authority PFI projects through the revenue support grant system. <br><br><br>The Coalition Government has strongly emphasised securing value for money from PFI including savings through its Operational Savings Programme. This Department has achieved programme savings of £497 million since 2010 from projects during procurement and savings from operational PFI projects of £33 million.<br><br>Details of local authority sponsored PFI projects can be found on the government website at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/pfi-projects-data-march-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects=2013-summary-data. <br></a><br>This currently provides information as at 31st March 2013 but will be updated shortly with data as at 31st March 2014.<br><br></p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-05T16:17:01.8474573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92911/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92911/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92912","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-20","<p>DCMS has given undertakings to providing revenue support to a range of library and leisure schemes across England, consistent with the long term nature of PFI contracts.</p><p> </p><p>Based on current levels of agreed revenue support, the forecast liability for the next 20 years would be £481m at today’s prices.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-20T15:43:55.9626387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92912/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92912/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210084"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92913","Department for Education","false","2014-10-20","<p>The Department for Education sponsors local authority projects through the private finance initiative (PFI) credit system and is paying revenue support grant. It also contributes revenue support towards Voluntary Aided school PFI schemes. However, these are not the Department’s liabilities.</p><p> </p><p>Details of these projects are available online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data</a>.</p><p> </p><p>This currently provides information as at 31 March 2013 but will be updated shortly with data as at 31 March 2014.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-10-20T15:12:26.6269225Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92913/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92913/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of her Department are for the next 20 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92914","Cabinet Office","false","2014-10-16","<p>Information on the Cabinet Office’s expenditure under Private Finance Initiative contracts is available in the department’s Annual Report and Accounts 2013-14 (pages 156 to 157), available in the Library of the House and on the GOV.UK website below at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/cabinet-office-annual-reports-and-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/cabinet-office-annual-reports-and-accounts</a></p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-10-16T07:40:38.7425806Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92914/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92914/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92915","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-24","<p><strong>The Treasury holds one PFI project, GOGGS West, which will come to a close in 2037-38.</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>Further information on current PFI and PF2 projects can be found on the following link, <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data</a>. </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>This data will be updated in due course, in the normal way.</strong></p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-10-24T13:38:22.4072874Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92915/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92915/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92916","Attorney General","false","2014-10-20","<p>The total private finance initiative liabilities (PFI) of the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) for the next 20 years are set out in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>£'000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£'000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£’000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5,933</p></td><td><p>4,554</p></td><td><p>10,487</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Under their current terms the CPS’s two PFI contracts are set to expire at the end of November 2015. The CPS PFI liabilities will therefore end in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The figures contained in the table above are drawn from Note 16 of the CPS 2013/14 Annual Report and Accounts, ‘Commitments under PFI contracts’.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The remaining Law Officers’ Departments do not have any PFI liabilities.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Mr Robert Buckland",,"2014-10-20T15:40:38.056186Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92916/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92916/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of the Law Officers' Departments are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92917","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-20","<p>The Departmental Group is involved in two private finance initiatives; an IT infrastructure initiative managed by the Insolvency Service, and a Research Ship managed by the Natural Environment Research Council. The table below sets out the annual unitary payments for the next 20 years as at 31 March 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Project</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18</strong></p><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018-19</strong></p><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2019-20</strong></p><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Research Ship</strong></p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>1.6</p></td><td><p>1.6</p></td><td><p>1.6</p></td><td><p>1.6</p></td><td><p>0.6</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>IT Infrastructure</strong></p></td><td><p>2.4</p></td><td><p>2.3</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>2.0</p></td><td><p>2.0</p></td><td><p>0.2</p></td><td><p>11.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p>4.6</p></td><td><p>3.9</p></td><td><p>3.8</p></td><td><p>3.6</p></td><td><p>3.6</p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>20.3</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-10-20T15:00:18.6299029Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92917/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92917/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210080"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92918","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-21","<p>The sanctions have been designed to have the maximum impact on the actions of the Russian leadership while minimising the impact on the UK and EU. There will be a cost to the EU's economy, but there is a greater cost involved in not standing up to Russia's aggression. The Government has been clear that any pain as a result of economic sanctions should be shared equally across the EU.</p><p> </p><p>Due to the recent nature of the implementation of the sanctions Treasury officials are still in the process of analysing the initial data; it is a work in progress and not yet ready for public use.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-10-21T09:10:18.2048832Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92918/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92918/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-13","Russia","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of sanctions against the Russian Federation on the UK economy; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92919","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-20","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) has only one private finance initiative liability. This is in relation to the British Embassy in Berlin. The FCO Berlin Private Finance Initiative (PFI) liability (the Unitary Payment) expires in June 2030. The Unitary Payment under the PFI agreement is annually indexed using an agreed index formula. The value of the PFI is commercially sensitive, as the release of such information would likely be commercially disadvantageous to the FCO when tendering future contracts as part of the initiative.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-10-20T16:31:53.0144935Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92919/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92919/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92920","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-20","<p>The total Private Finance Initiative (PFI) liability for the Ministry of Defence (MOD) over the next 20 years is £29.4 billion. The table shows the forecast annual payment (the unitary charge) due for all current MOD PFI contracts. <br><br>Year Estimated unitary charge (£ billion)<br>2014-15 (part year) 0.974<br>2015-16 1.837<br>2016-17 1.664<br>2017-18 1.666<br>2018-19 1.692<br>2019-20 1.726<br>2020-21 1.745<br>2021-22 1.727<br>2022-23 1.590<br>2023-24 1.403<br>2024-25 1.409<br>2025-26 1.367<br>2026-27 1.405<br>2027-28 1.407<br>2028-29 1.424<br>2029-30 1.356<br>2030-31 1.257<br>2031-32 1.224<br>2032-33 1.197<br>2033-34 0.889<br>2034-35 (part year) 0.440<br><br>The current MOD PFI portfolio covers 41 projects, including the Strategic Sealift Roll-on Roll-off Ferry and Heavy Equipment Transporter logistics vehicle, which directly support the front line. PFI arrangements are also used for a range of accommodation and infrastructure projects.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-20T15:52:28.5503448Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92920/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92920/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92921","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-10-20","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Change has no private financial initiative liabilities.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-10-20T13:59:04.5560945Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92921/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92921/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92922","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-20","<p>Core Defra has one private finance initiative (PFI) project for which Defra has future liabilities. The details of this can be found on the attached spreadsheet.</p><p> </p><p>Core Defra has also sponsored a number of local authority projects through the PFI credit system. These are not liabilities of the Department. Details of these can be found at the following link. This currently provides data as at 31 March 2013 but will be updated shortly with data as at 31 March 2014.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data</a></p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-10-20T16:50:44.2173289Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92922/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92922/answer","0576 - PFI attachment.xls","0576 - PFI attachment.xls","PFI Attachment","PFI Attachment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92922/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of her Department are for the next 20 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92923","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-18","<p>The MoJ (the core Department and its Executive Agencies) had Private Finance Initiative liabilities of £4,420,376,000 as at 31 March 2014. These liabilities related to 22 contracts, the details of which are in the table attached.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-11-18T13:32:44.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92923/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92923/answer","Table of PFI Liabilities.doc","Table of PFI Liabilities.doc","Table of PFI Liabilities","Table of PFI Liabilities","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92923/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92924","Home Office","false","2014-10-17","<p>The unitary charge for the 2 Marsham Street PFI project (the Home Office HQ) from financial year 2014/15 to 2030/31 (when the contract finishes) is estimated to be £883.22 million.<br><br>The unitary charge for the Airwave programme from 2014/15 until 2020 (when the contract finishes) is forecasted to be £872.42 million.<br><br>The Home Office provides revenue support grants to a number of Police and Crime Commissioners (PCCs) who have a PFI project in their force area. The total amount of resource grant from financial year 2014/15 until 2034/35 is estimated to be £1.4 billion.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-10-17T15:27:04.0698774Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92924/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92924/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of her Department are for the next 20 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92925","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-20","<p>DFID has not entered into any Private Finance Initiatives (PFIs). Therefore the total liability for PFIs per the DFID Annual Report and Accounts as at 31 March 2014 and 30 September 2014 is £0.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-10-20T16:36:15.8015524Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92925/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92925/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of her Department are for the next 20 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92926","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-20","<p /> <p><strong>The Department has three current private finance initiative contracts:</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>1. </strong><strong>The Private Sector Resource Initiative for the Management of the Estate (PRIME)</strong>. A 20 year PFI partnership awarded on 1<sup>st</sup> April 1998 to Trillium (now Telereal Trillium). PRIME delivered a transfer of property ownership of the DWP estate and outsourced most facilities management services. The PRIME contractor is responsible for all landlord and property related tasks, delivers a total maintenance programme and provides all building related services.</p><p> </p><p><strong>2. </strong><strong>Health and Safety Laboratory, Buxton</strong>. A 30 year contract awarded on 1<sup>st</sup> April 2002 to Interserve plc.</p><p> </p><p><strong>3. </strong><strong>Health and Safety Executive, New Merseyside Centre, Redgrave Court, Bootle</strong>. A 30 year contract awarded on 1<sup>st</sup> October 2003 to Honeywell Control Systems, supported by Reliance FM as the prime facilities management provider.</p><p> </p><p>The remaining financial liabilities for each contract between 2014/15 and its expiry date are:</p><p> </p><p>PRIME 2014/15 to 2017/18 £2,074.47m</p><p>HSL 2014/15 to 2034/5 £278.79m</p><p>HSE 2014/15 to 2034/5 £244.73m</p><p> </p><p><strong>Total £2,597.99m</strong></p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-20T13:22:42.945615Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92926/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92926/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92927","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-17","<p>I refer the hon, member to the Written Ministerial Statement made by my Rt. Hon. Friend, Iain Duncan Smith on Monday 13<sup>th</sup> October 2014.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-vote-office/2014-October/13th%20October/17.DWP-welfare-reform.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-vote-office/2014-October/13th%20October/17.DWP-welfare-reform.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State announced the next stage of implementing Universal Credit to all remaining Jobcentres and Local Authorities as we progress national expansion through 2015/16 and secure delivery of Universal Credit across Great Britain.</p><p> </p><p>Currently, officials in my Department are working with delivery partners on the detailed schedule for national roll out. The finalised details will be made available in due course.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-17T11:02:01.3761353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92927/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92927/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-13","Universal Credit: Brighton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the timetable is for the implementation of universal credit in Brighton and Hove; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92928","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-10-20","<p>My Department does not currently have any private finance initiative liabilities.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-10-20T10:06:56.3805526Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92928/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92928/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of her Department are for the next 20 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92929","Wales Office","false","2014-10-20","<p>The Wales Office does not have any private finance initiative liabilities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2014-10-20T09:20:36.2027008Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92929/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92929/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92930","Department for Transport","false","2014-10-20","<p><strong>The Department has the following liabilities over the next 20 years under the private finance initiative contracts to which it is counterparty:</strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>These are the latest available figures and represent the forecast nominal cash payments due under the contracts over this period (2014-15 to 2033-34).</strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>The Department also provides financial support to Local Authorities for a number of private finance initiative transport projects, though these are not the Department’s liabilities. Further information on these Local Authority sponsored projects can be found at the following web address. This currently provides information as at 31 March 2013 but will be updated shortly with data as at 31 March 2014:</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-projects-2013-summary-data</a></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-10-20T16:15:02.7630148Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92930/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92930/answer","210095.xlsx","210095.xlsx","Table","Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92930/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-10-13","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the total private finance initiative liabilities of his Department are for the next 20 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","210095"
