"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93054","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-16","<p>The law on joint enterprise means that if two or more people share an intention to commit an offence and the offence is subsequently committed, all parties involved can be prosecuted for that offence. They may also be liable for any collateral offences which they foresaw might be committed by other members of the group in the course of putting their plan into effect. But they would not be liable for any offences that were fundamentally different from anything they foresaw or if they had taken steps to withdraw from the enterprise before the plan was carried out.</p><p> </p><p>The law serves a useful purpose in bringing to justice all those who have been involved in the commission of an offence. We therefore have no plans to review or amend it during the life time of this Parliament or to meet with representatives of the campaign group Joint Enterprise: Not Guilty by Association.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","210215","2014-10-16T14:08:02.9479928Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93054/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93054/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-10-13","Aiding and Abetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans he has to bring forward  proposals to reform joint enterprise legislation in the 2010-15 Parliament.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","210143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93055","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-16","<p>The law on joint enterprise means that if two or more people share an intention to commit an offence and the offence is subsequently committed, all parties involved can be prosecuted for that offence. They may also be liable for any collateral offences which they foresaw might be committed by other members of the group in the course of putting their plan into effect. But they would not be liable for any offences that were fundamentally different from anything they foresaw or if they had taken steps to withdraw from the enterprise before the plan was carried out.</p><p> </p><p>The law serves a useful purpose in bringing to justice all those who have been involved in the commission of an offence. We therefore have no plans to review or amend it during the life time of this Parliament or to meet with representatives of the campaign group Joint Enterprise: Not Guilty by Association.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","210143","2014-10-16T14:08:03.2136086Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93055/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93055/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-10-13","Aiding and Abetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will meet the Joint Enterprise: Not Guilty by Association campaigners.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","210215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93056","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-16","<p>In November 2013, RBS established RBS Capital Resolution (RCR), an internal bad bank, in order to separate and wind down RBS’s poorly-performing and high-risk assets. RBS transferred £38 billion of ‘high-risk’ legacy assets to RCR. RCR is managed separately from the main bank, and the aim is to wind down these assets in full within three years. As a result, there is not any intention to transfer additional assets in or out of RCR.</p><p> </p><p>Further details on the operations, objectives and composition of loans in RCR can be found in the Government’s Bad Bank Review available at:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/rbs-and-the-case-for-a-bad-bank-the-governments-review</p><p> </p><p>RBS also produces detailed reporting updates on the progress of RCR alongside its financial results, which are available on the RBS website.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","210140 ; 210141","2014-10-16T13:43:01.2640552Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93056/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93056/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-10-13","RBS Capital Resolution","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he has taken to ensure that businesses in the RBS Capital Resolution bank are restored to the good bank within RBS.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","210142"
